With the mask you wore to hide your identity during
the killing planted in Prince Juno's room, along with
his katana being found on King Tem's body, he has been
found guilty, leaving you free from your wrong doing.
Now Prince Louis shall become King, and with his
popularity he quickly became a hero to the people after
his father's tyranny. However, as the years went on his
need to be loved only grew, and one by one his kingly
tasks faded into the background, leaving much the same
poverty caused by his father's corruption to fester,
while Louis continued to ensure those around him held
him in high regard. As such the cycle of neglect
begun by his father would continue under Louis, causing
the same resentment to grow, no matter how much he
tried to make the people love him again.
With the mask you wore to hide your identity during
the killing planted in Prince Louis' room, along with
his hairpin being found on King Tem's body, he has been
found guilty, leaving you free from your wrong doing.
Now Prince Juno shall become King, and for him this
acted as a opportunity to finally put into practice the
many progressive policies he had been concieving of for
countless years. These changes would reverse the
horrors seen under King Tem, and usher in a new era
of prosperity for the Kingdom. However, few truly knew
Juno, as he would rarely make public appearances, and
the few times he would they rarely made him look good.
As such, other members of the nobility were able to
take this opportunity to rally the people to their
side, eventually leading to a full blown revolution
which would topple Juno from his throne and install a
new house of nobility to the throne, one which shared
more in common with King Tem than Juno, and would
reverse his policies in favour of ones which would
benefit their family instead.
